Our little family loves going to Muller's Factory for breakfast, lunch and dinner. We find it hard to choose between the delicious sweet crêpes or waffles (my favourite is the Swiss grated chocolate with banana slices inside the waffle) and the amazing and filling savoury Crêpes (Mamma Mia or La Muller's are to die for). We actually love crêpes so much that we often pass by the shop to just buy the crêpe batter to make lazy crêpes at home on a Sunday morning...

Also, if you happen to be going during winter - make sure to try their home-made mulled wine when its available (best in Geneva) or other yummy hot beverages! reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Anoop Chana', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108609904401435911101/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AItbvmmDBdujDVJO-I3-pgyfuOtmq6xTtCgo1KxQwPjx=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'The best Resturant in Geneva overall. I have eaten at some of the finest restaurants across Lisbon, Porto and Faro, and this restaurant replicates, and goes further, that feeling and experience of fine Portuguese cuisine. I would even recommend for a romantic meal for those that want an evening of fine wine, fine food and fine conversation 😊', 'time': 1635855406}, {'author_name': 'Geneva Sam', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112917871961218846292/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AFdZucqbBVwB8R2nCEWsLGglTVqEwPElTo2kyRVn8bvKzA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'It was our first experience in a Portuguese restaurant and the Manager helped select the menu. He brought a tray of starters saying it was "complimentary", followed by the main course we ordered.  I asked for normal tap water which was also provided,  but when the bill came included chf 2.50 for the water. Upon querying he replied that they charge to cover expenses. Sadly it was disappointing for a otherwise pleasant experience', 'time': 1631215886}, {'author_name': 'Warthain', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110525760708885985598/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AFdZucpeyp6k9BH2sBfoziHBLp70-KJgUkM2_prWfl0zrQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Good food, good pricing and good service, need me to say anything else?', 'time': 1635505566}, {'author_name': 'José Maçãs', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117304623142785191313/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AFdZucor-fsC_NogqEDMQlpYVzVL4gvZR9dQWV4R5Z1RCg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "It's always hard to find a good portuguese restaurant out of Portugal.

I discovered Boa Brasa in Geneva almost 2 years ago and I've been a regular client since then and hosted a few events for friends and co-workers.

This restaurant meets all the requirements I would have back home in terms of food - grilled fish, octopus, meat (sourced from 'Boucherie du Molard'), traditional and elaborated courses or the simple & delicious starters like 'alheira' and pica-pau'. The wine list is quite complete and do ask the owner for good recommendations on the region and / or price range you are looking for.

Pedro and Silvia are great hosts and the chef runs an impecable & swift kitchen.

Notes: 1) book in advance if you plan to go on the weekend and 2) arrive ahead of time as parking slots are limited in neighborhood. Even better, take an Uber and enjoy a good wine without concerns :)", 'time': 1624302664}, {'author_name': 'Joao Amaral', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107754251426194559574/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AFdZucr2Djb2n648T0ml-OSEnIE3xEkQfrEDWl6SxakpwQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'Very good food and nice people. name: Burger King
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Star Health', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106612019152706081223/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AItbvmkPq8cn2IF7HYX7Bl3Ql0MimGbyqAxhgr7NgAKG=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'One of the worst restaurant I have ever went to. I ordered a big milkshake and paid for it already, but the milkshake machine is broken. An employee then asked me if I want my money back or they will give me a small ice cream to change the milkshake. I asked her if I can just get my money back. After that, maybe she didn\'t know how to refund the money, so she called her manager to help. Then her manager on a wheelchair came to see us. After knowing that I want a refund, he yelled at me saying that why did I order the milkshake and after don\'t want it and just want it to be refunded. Then, I and the employee explained the situation to him. However, he was still mad at me, yelled at the employee to give me the ice cream by force and yelled at me again to just get the ice cream and no refund will be issued and to get out of the restaurant, without even saying sorry or any kind of apologizing. I just said to myself "whatever with this guy" and just left the restaurant because I have a bus and a train to catch. The price of the "small ice cream" is not even the same as the "big milkshake" because the ice cream is a lot cheaper than the milkshake. Never coming back to this burger king ever again.', 'time': 1657023574}]

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Joel Hames', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102174150868236962938/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AFdZucreXBP6pAlVGruQJ24YMsgPwHTza3-cXphCcdF9WA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'This one is tough. Short version is that the food was really good, especially the fish and the risotto. If you love truffle, you’ll love the flavor of the food here. The wine selection was good, too.

As usual in this area, the service itself was a bit slow. But the bigger issue, the thing keeping this from being 5 stars, is that it just didn’t have the value we were hoping for. At the cost of these dishes, we expected something a bit more elegant and refined. Certainly the truffle focus was solid, but beyond that it felt like most other decent restaurants in the area. For what we were paying, I was hoping to walk away more impressed than I was.

It’s definitely worth a visit. I don’t think you’ll leave disappointed with the quality of the food. But temper your expectations if you are going in for something particularly special.
